formkeylist: Did Incision Need to be Enlarged?:
Is the product: tablets/capsules; liquids; or powder/granules.
• Is the bottle glass or plastic?
• Was the prescription dispensed in an original manufacturer’s bottle/package, or a pharmacy bottle or in a customer’s own container?
• Is the bottle empty; or is it underfilled or overfilled?
• If the container is empty, is there any residue in the package or is it completely empty?
• Does this bottle have a seal?
• If there should be a seal, was the seal intact or was it missing or torn or unsealed?
• If the product is overfilled, by how much is the product overfilled?
• If product is underfilled, by how much is the product underfilled?
• How does the customer know it is underfilled or overfilled (measured each dose, counted etc.)
• If product is a liquid or powder, was each dose measured?
• If yes, what was used to measure the dose?
• For NOXAFIL: Was the dosing spoon that is included with the product used when administering the medication?
• When was the shortage or overage noted?
• If after use, how many doses were previously used?
• Was there any damage to the primary container and/or the cap?
